<leg xml:space="preserve" billnum="HB0164" sponsor="Stephanie Gricius" designation="HB" otherSponsor="Stephanie Pitcher" otherHouse="Senate" sess="2026GS" fileno="2026FL0023" date="1/7/2026 10:01:100" printDate="01-29 10:49" subVer="0" minVer="0" office="LEGISLATIVE GENERAL COUNSEL" actionDate="" impact="code"><info><nextbuid>8</nextbuid><aminfo anum="0" effdate="05/06/2026"><seclist><sect action="A" src="code" buid="6" uid="C26B-2-S221_2026050620260506" fromuid="C26B-2-S221_2023050320230503" sort="26B02 02210020260506" mtype="section" effdate="05/06/2026">26B-2-221</sect><sect src="uncod" untype="effdate" buid="7" uid="EF0000" sort="UZEFF" mtype="uncod" effdate="05/06/2026"/></seclist></aminfo></info><tbox><sinfo><nextpairid>0</nextpairid></sinfo><st numlevel="1" lineno="1" slineno="0-1">Patient Disclosure Amendments</st><sessionhead>2026 GENERAL SESSION</sessionhead><statehead>STATE OF UTAH</statehead><sponsorhead>Chief Sponsor: Stephanie Gricius</sponsorhead><otherSponsorhead>Senate Sponsor: Stephanie Pitcher</otherSponsorhead></tbox><lt numlevel="1" lineno="2" slineno="0-2"><lthead lineno="3">LONG TITLE</lthead><gdhead lineno="4">General Description:</gdhead><gd numlevel="1" lineno="5" slineno="0-5">This bill requires health care providers to inform patients how the patient can report <ln numlevel="1" lineno="6" slineno="0-6"/>unprofessional or unlawful conduct in certain circumstances.</gd><hphead lineno="7">Highlighted Provisions:</hphead><hp numlevel="1" lineno="8" slineno="0-8">This bill:<hl numlevel="1" lineno="9" slineno="0-9" level="1">requires health care providers that receive a disclosure of potential unprofessional or <ln numlevel="1" lineno="10" slineno="0-10"/>unlawful conduct to provide information about how to report the concern to the Division <ln numlevel="1" lineno="11" slineno="0-11"/>of Professional Licensing.</hl></hp><moni numlevel="1" lineno="12" slineno="0-12" display="none">Money Appropriated in this Bill:</moni><moniNone lineno="13">None</moniNone><oc numlevel="1" lineno="14" slineno="0-14">Other Special Clauses:</oc><ocNone lineno="15">None</ocNone><sa numlevel="1" lineno="16" slineno="0-16">Utah Code Sections Affected:<saamd numlevel="1" lineno="17" slineno="0-17"><snhead>AMENDS:</snhead><sn num="26B-2-221" src="code" uid="C26B-2-S221_2026050620260506" buid="6" sort="26B02 02210020260506" numlevel="1" lineno="18" slineno="0-18"><bold>26B-2-221</bold>, as renumbered and amended by Laws of Utah 2023, Chapter 305</sn></saamd></sa></lt><enacthead lineno="19"/><enact numlevel="1" lineno="20" slineno="0-20">Be it enacted by the Legislature of the state of Utah:</enact><bdy><bsec buid="6" num="26B-2-221" type="amend" src="code" uid="C26B-2-S221_2026050620260506" sort="26B02 02210020260506" numlevel="1" lineno="21" slineno="1-1" sn="1"><section number="26B-2-221" numlevel="1" lineno="22" slineno="1-2" type="amend"><secline lineno="21">Section 1. Section <bold>26B-2-221</bold> is amended to read:</secline><catline lineno="22"><bold>26B-2-221<parens/>. Reporting health care providers.</bold></catline><subsection ssid="6-1" dnum="_-o:1-i" numlevel="1" lineno="23" slineno="1-3" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="ahaskell" style="1" level="1" placement="noreturn"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1000" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="both">(1)</amend></display>A health care facility licensed under this part which reports disciplinary <ln numlevel="1" lineno="24" slineno="1-4"/>information on a licensed nurse to the Division of Professional Licensing within the <ln numlevel="1" lineno="25" slineno="1-5"/>Department of Commerce as required by Section <xref depth="3" refnumber="58-31b-702" start="0">58-31b-702</xref> is entitled to the immunity <ln numlevel="1" lineno="26" slineno="1-6"/>from liability provided by that section.</subsection><subsection ssid="6-2" dnum="_-o:2-i" numlevel="1" lineno="27" slineno="1-7" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="ahaskell" style="1" level="1"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1001" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(2)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="8" groupid="7" style="1" owner="ahaskell" level="1" amendtag="end">A health care provider or a health care provider's employee shall provide, in writing at <ln numlevel="1" lineno="28" slineno="1-8"/>the time of the disclosure, information about how an individual may file a complaint <ln numlevel="1" lineno="29" slineno="1-9"/>with the Division of Professional Licensing if the individual discloses a concern about a <ln numlevel="1" lineno="30" slineno="1-10"/>current or former provider's potential unprofessional or unlawful conduct.</amend></subsection></section></bsec><bsec buid="7" type="uncod" untype="effdate" src="uncod" uid="EF0000" sort="UZEFF" langlock="true" numlevel="1" lineno="31" slineno="2-1" sn="2"><section type="uncod" untype="effdate" display="false" src="uncod"><secline lineno="31">Section 2.  <bold>Effective Date.</bold></secline><sectionText lineno="32"><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1" groupid="1" style="1" owner="ahaskell" level="1" amendtag="both">This bill takes effect on <effdate uid="code" date="5/6/2026">May 6, 2026</effdate>.</amend></sectionText></section></bsec></bdy><foot><rev><tm>1-7-26 10:42 AM</tm></rev></foot></leg>